credit_line: Gift of Stephen W. Brener and Carol B. Brener
title: Emperor Napoleon III
provenance: Collection of Carol B. Brener and Stephen W. Brener
description: Circular, in the shape of a five Franc coin, with raised decoration of the Emperor in profile with laurel wreath on his head, inscribed on perimeter "Napoleon III, Empereur," "Barre" inscribed below, reverse features coat-of-arms, inscribed "Empire Francais, 5F, 1870." Wedge shaped piece swings out of container at top to reveal interior match compartment. Striker attached to side.
name: Matchsafe
